                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-24T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 24, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 24—1:43 a.
                        m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>606. China Customs [head] L. K. Little, having transferred headquarters here, had
                    long talk Generalissimo latter’s request—who, although claiming unofficial
                    status, proceeded give orders. Generalissimo seriously worried over danger
                    invasion Formosa and wants customs boat for defense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
